description:
&nbsp;   
   Reference    : LOM-24-05-0051&nbsp;  
   Title    : Quantifying invasion dynamics: qPCR vs. ddPCR in monitoring the alien invasive bloody-red shrimp  Hemimysis anomala  and its interaction with perch in Lake Geneva  
  Authors  : Sirine Melliti, Marine Vautier, C&eacute;cile Chardon, St&eacute;phan Jacquet 
  Correspondence  : St&eacute;phan Jacquet, UMR CARRTEL, 75bis Avenue de Corzent, 74203 Thonon-les-Bains Cedex, France.  E-mail:    stephan.jacquet@inrae.fr      
  &nbsp;  
  This file is composed by 3 different sheets&nbsp;  
   "DNA concentration" sheet:&nbsp;    
  - Calculations to get, from copies/&mu;L reaction, copies/Litre of filtered water for  Hemimysis anomala  and  Perca fluviatilis  for ddPCR   
  -  Concentrations  in copies/L of filtered water for  Hemimysis anomala  for qPCR&nbsp;  
   "qPCR vs ddPCR" sheet:    
  Log  Hemimysis anomala  DNA concentrations (copies/L filtered water) for qPCR and ddPCR&nbsp;  
   "LOD-LOQ" sheet:    
  Calculations of the Limits of Detection and Quantitation for the ddPCR based on a range of 8 successive concentrations of  Hemimysis anomala  with 5 replicates   
   - &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;     LOD (the lowest concentration at which the target DNA was detected in at least one replicate)   
   - &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;     LOQ (the lowest concentration with a coefficient of variation value of less than 35%)

